title: Mass Effect - Revelation by Drew Karpyshyn
description:
Book Description
================
Every advanced society in the galaxy relies on the technology of the 
Protheans, an ancient species that vanished fifty thousand years ago. 
After discovering a cache of Prothean technology on Mars in 2148, humanity 
is spreading to the stars; the newest interstellar species, struggling 
to carve out its place in the greater galactic community.

On the edge of colonized space, ship commander and Alliance war hero 
David Anderson investigates the remains of a top secret military research 
station; smoking ruins littered with bodies and unanswered questions. 
Who attacked this post and for what purpose? And where is Kahlee Sanders, 
the young scientist who mysteriously vanished from the base - hours 
before her colleagues were slaughtered?

Sanders is now the prime suspect, but finding her creates more problems 
for Anderson than it solves. Partnered with a rogue alien agent he can't 
trust and pursued by an assassin he can't escape, Anderson battles impossible 
odds on uncharted worlds to uncover a sinister conspiracy . . . one 
he won't live to tell about. Or so the enemy thinks.
